<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880505-0073 </DOCNO><HL> DNA Plant Technology </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DNAP AGSI </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> CINNAMINSON, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   DNA Plant Technology Corp. and Advanced Genetic Sciences Inc. said they reached new terms for the merger of the two companies.    The terms now provide that holders of Advanced Genetic will receive one-half share of DNA Plant Technology, instead of two-thirds of a share as under the previous terms, for each share of Advanced Genetic.    DNA Plant Technology, based here, and Advanced Genetic, Oakland, Calif., both have interests in agricultural biotechnology. </TEXT></DOC>